Third-party code and attribution
=================================

Spicy EX renders Spicy-Lyrics-style animated lyrics inside the Spotify Android
app. Portions of the lyric rendering, animation, and parsing logic are derived
from the following AGPL-3.0 projects; the conveyed binary as a whole is therefore
licensed under AGPL-3.0:

- Spicy Lyrics  — https://github.com/Spikerko/spicy-lyrics  (AGPL-3.0)
    Animation engine, gradient/karaoke wash, lyric parsing model.
- Better Lyrics / braccato — https://github.com/boidushya/better-lyrics  (AGPL-3.0)
    Lyric engine reference.
- kawarp (@kawarp/core) — https://github.com/better-lyrics/kawarp  (AGPL-3.0)
    Domain-warp + Kawase-blur animated background; ported to an AGSL RuntimeShader.

Behavior reimplemented from observation, public specifications, or factual data
(CSS values, spring/falloff math, BGN/PCGN romanization tables, kawarp's
technique) is independent work, as is the original SpotifyPlus base and Spicy EX's
own romanization (Korean G2P, Cyrillic Russian/Ukrainian).

The SpotifyPlus-origin files retain their original MIT notices where present.
